        <compounds>
          <compound>
            <id type="integer">1916</id>
            <name>Carbonic acid</name>
            <hmdb-id>HMDB0003538</hmdb-id>
            <description>Carbonic acid (ancient name acid of air or aerial acid) is the only inorganic carbon acid, and has the formula H2CO3. It is also a name sometimes given to solutions of carbon dioxide in water, which contain small amounts of H2CO3. The salts of carbonic acids are called bicarbonates (or hydrogencarbonates) and carbonates. (wikipedia).</description>
